in home environment."

167
00:12:16,920 --> 00:12:20,037
"No criminal record.
School records will be checked."

168
00:12:28,600 --> 00:12:31,990
- Do I get a job from you?
- Yes, but you'll have to wait in the queue.

169
00:12:32,080 --> 00:12:35,152
- You get me a job, right?
- Yes, but you can't jump the queue.

170
00:12:35,240 --> 00:12:38,232
And you're supposed not to
take the cards from the display.

171
00:12:38,320 --> 00:12:40,276
Could you put them back for me?

172
00:12:40,360 --> 00:12:42,316
Tacky jobs, ain't they?

173
00:12:42,400 --> 00:12:44,868
If you wait, perhaps
we can sort something out!

174
00:12:44,960 --> 00:12:48,236
You got something useful I can do
while I'm waiting for a job?

175
00:12:48,320 --> 00:12:51,710
I got ten O levels, seven A levels,
I speak Punjabi and chapatti!

176
00:12:51,800 --> 00:12:53,756
You'll have to wait!

177
00:12:56,520 --> 00:12:58,476
I'll come back tomorrow.

178
00:13:02,120 --> 00:13:04,588
<i>- (youth) See ya!
- I doubt it.</i>

179
00:13:34,960 --> 00:13:36,916
What's this place?

180
00:14:16,680 --> 00:14:18,636
Where did you get all them?

181
00:14:18,720 --> 00:14:20,676
